   <head>D. Boners woordes.</head>
   <p>¶ If thou at anye tyme heretofore haue doubted, of the B. of Romes false pretenced supremacie, as <note place="margin">In praef.</note> if thou haddest a good smelling nose, and a sounde judgement, I thinke thou dydest not: yet hauinge reade ouer this, which (if thou fauour the truethe, and hate the tyrannie of the Busshop of Rome and his Deuelishe fraudulent falshod,) shall doubtles wonderfullye content the, throwe downe thine er<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>rour, &amp; acknowledge the truethe, now frelye offe<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>red the at length: consideringe with thy selfe, that it is better late to do so, then neuer to repente.</p>
